638:     /// Collects all macro invocations reachable at this time in this AST fragment, and replace
639:     /// them with "placeholders" - dummy macro invocations with specially crafted `NodeId`s.
640:     /// Then call into resolver that builds a skeleton ("reduced graph") of the fragment and
641:     /// prepares data for resolving paths of macro invocations.
642:     fn collect_invocations(
